Program: Outlook
Title: George Alagiah on Becoming British
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbsmb
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
Sri Lankan-born BBC reporter George Alagiah on immigration and how he became British. Also, why wearing your pyjamas in public in Shanghai offends the neighbours. The Iraqi father whose five haemophiliac sons died from AIDS contracted from tainted blood products. Finally, the Hindu Monk running a leprosy clinic in India; Presenter: Heather Payton. Show less